<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-03-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-03-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="1525" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1525">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 17554/22.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Chargé d’Affaires at
                                Lima</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-03-11">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 11, 1910</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your March 7. This Department would sincerely deplore haste or severance
                            of diplomatic relations between Chile and Peru on account of dispute
                            over status of priests at Tacna. Department believes that at present the
                            giving of instructions to our Chargé d’Affaires at Santiago to take
                            charge of Peruvian Legation would be premature.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>